<Aside title="Self-hosting required" type="note">
  ENSDb is available when you <a href="/docs/self-host">self-host ENSNode</a>.
  Each ENSNode instance writes its data into a PostgreSQL database that you own and control — that database <strong>is</strong> your ENSDb instance.
  The hosted ENSNode instances do not expose direct database access.
</Aside>
